sequenceDiagram  
 participant CC as MCP Client
participant B as Browser
participant S as MCP Server

      CC->>S: GET /mcp (no token)
      S-->>CC: 401 Unauthorized<br/>WWW-Authenticate: Bearer resource_metadata=".../.well-known/oauth-protected-resource"

      CC->>S: GET /.well-known/oauth-protected-resource
      S-->>CC: { resource, authorization_servers }

      CC->>S: GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server
      S-->>CC: { authorization_endpoint, token_endpoint, registration_endpoint, ... }

      CC->>S: POST /oauth/register
      S-->>CC: { client_id }

      CC->>B: Open browser → GET /oauth/authorize?client_id=...&code_challenge=...&state=...
      B->>S: GET /oauth/authorize
      S-->>B: Render HTML login form

      B->>S: POST /oauth/authorize (email + password + OAuth params)
      Note over S: Validate credentials <br/>Generate one-time code → store in AuthorizationCodeStore
      S-->>B: 302 Redirect → redirect_uri?code=&state=

      B->>CC: Callback with code + state

      CC->>S: POST /oauth/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code, code, code_verifier
      Note over S: Validate code → verify PKCE<br/>Generate Access And Refresh Tokens
      S-->>CC: { access_token, refresh_token, expires_in }

      CC->>S: GET /mcp (Authorization: Bearer access_token)
      S-->>CC: MCP response ✓